
	
	
React in existing web Application:

1. create a new folder for project at any location on your device 
	
2. Open project folder in visual studino code editor
3. Run the following command in project terminal
> npm init -y 
(it generate "package.json", which comprises of project meta data.)

4. Add following files & folder into project
			README.md files

			File/Folder				Description
			Package.json			project meta data
			Readme.md				help document by developer for developers
			.gitignore 				congiguration of files to ignore while publishing on to GIT
			public 					comprises of static resources like HTML, Images , documents[pdf,docx,xslx,mkv, avi, json]
			src 					comprises of dynamic resources like sass, css , js jsx ts, tsx etc
			index.html 				startup page for application

	
5.Add a new page "home.html" into public folder

6. Add <noscript>element into body section it is used to verify the status of javascript in browser.

		<noscript>
			please enable jabascript on your browser
		</noscript>
		
7. Add a root container into actual DOM which renders the content from Virtual DOM

			<div id="root"></div>

8. To enable React in any HTML page you need following libraries

		a) React	  : it is the core react library that provides all react function.
		b) react-dom  : it is library of creating and handling Virtual Dom.
		c) babel	  : it is a javascript compiler
		
		javascript? javascript is a light weight interpreted and jit compiled programming language. 
		jit -> just in  time
		aot -> head of time
		
	-React upto 18x version provides CDN for 'react & react-dom'.
		https://legacy.reactjs.org/ => docs => CDN
		
		-Copy cd for developement environment and paste into your HTML page <head> section.
		
		<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.development.js"></script>
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.development.js"></script>

	-Go to babel official website
	
	https://babeljs.io/ => docs => integrated Packages => @babe/shtandlone
	
	-Copy standlone CDN and paste into HTML page <head> below react-dom library.
	
	<script src="https://unpkg.com/@babel/standalone/babel.min.js"></script>
		
	-Add <script> element into <head> section with type as "text/babel"
	<script type="text/babel">
	</script>
	
	.Create a  virtual DOM and render into actual DOM 
	
	//React 17x
	
	ReactDOM.render("massage | component",document.getElementById("root"));
	
	//React 18x

 const root  = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
 root.render("massage|component");
 
 
 You can install all libraries into project
 
		>npm install react@18 react-dom@18 @babel/standalone --save 
		
		    <script src="../node_modules/react/umd/react.development.js" crossorigin></script>
			<script src="../node_modules/react-dom/umd/react-dom.development.js" crossorigin></script>
			<script src="../node_modules/@babel/standalone/babel.js"></script>
		
		-All library files are copied into "node_modules".
 
 
	











	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	